index 0000000..aabb1122
--- /dev/null
+++ b/north-transept/rose-window.md
@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+# North Rose Window — Specifications
+
+Also known as the *Rose du Nord* or *Window of the Glorification of the Virgin*.
+
+| Attribute       | Value                |
+|-----------------|----------------------|
+| Diameter        | 10.5 m               |
+| Date            | c. 1230              |
+| Central panel   | Virgin and Child     |
+| Surrounding     | Kings of Judah       |
+| Main color      | Chartres blue        |
+
+## Symbolism
+
+The central medallion depicts the Virgin Mary enthroned,
+surrounded by doves and angels. The twelve kings of Judah
+radiate outward in a geometric pattern that represents
+divine order.
+
+> "The north rose is a symphony in blue."
+> — Malcolm Miller, guide (1956–2023)

